    <div class="content" id="content">
    <h1>Undergraduate Programs</h1>

<p>
The Mathematics department offers two programs.
</p>
<p>
Our relatively new Financial Mathematics program brings together the best that Mathematics and Finance have to offer.  
Our highly motivated students take courses from both the Mathematics and Finance departments, along with electives from Computer
 Science and Business in a curriculum designed to offer maximum flexibility.
</p>
<p>
Our successful Mathematics and Its Applications program is designed to allow you to choose the direction 
of your education.  With special options in Computer Science and Economics or a wide variety of electives leading to minor, t
his program is suitable for those pursuing career goals in education, industry or higher education.
</p>
<p>
Please follow the links on the left to further explore these two exciting programs.
</p>
<p>
For inquiries and requests for further information for the Mathematics and Its Applications program, 
please contact the Program Director – Undergraduate Studies, <a href="http://math.ryerson.ca/people/ferrando.html" target="blank_">Dr. Sebastian Ferrando</a>, ferrando@ryerson.ca
</p>
<p>
For inquiries and requests for further information for the Financial Mathematics program, please 
contact the Program Director – Undergraduate Studies, <a href="http://math.ryerson.ca/people/olivares.html" target="blank_">
Dr. Pablo Olivares</a>, pablo.olivares@ryerson.ca
</p>










